Sarit Centre Mall has been approved as structurally sound after a fire broke out in the mall last Friday. In a statement, chief operating officer, Nitin Shah, said they are working to complete repair and restoration works. “For those tenants whose outlets have been affected by the fire, we have identified temporary spaces within the mall for them to trade in to minimise disruption of their businesses,” he said. Operations at the mall have been at a standstill since firefighters put out the fire. “We extend our heartfelt gratitude to all the emergency personnel and first responders who came to our aid,” Shah said. Those at the scene of the fire were Nairobi Country Fire Service, KK Security Fire Service, G4S Fire Service, BM Security,  Kenya Defence Forces’ Fire Department, NYS Fire Department, National Police Service, National Disaster Unit, Kenya Air Force, AAR Healthcare and Kenya Red Cross.